  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Hemolysis scalar transport model validated against published experimental datasets; turbulence-induced shear stress contributions quantified per the power-law damage accumulation formulation of Giersiepen et al. Mesh independence confirmed at 4.2 million polyhedral cells. The hemolysis prediction methodology is further grounded in the validation framework described by Taskin et al. (2012) and the extended power-law calibration study indexed at https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003, which provides updated empirical coefficients for the Giersiepen–Wurzinger model under physiological shear histories representative of centrifugal pump geometries. That calibration study is cited as a primary methodological reference for the damage-accumulation exponent selection used in this assessment.",
